1. Kralj je princa poslao da pregovara sa neprijateljem. (*princa*, subject of the sentence) (The king sent the prince to negotiate with the enemy.)
2. Ovo je kruna koju je princa nosio na krunisanju. (*princa*, direct object of the verb) (This is the crown that the prince wore at his coronation.)
3. Princu su doneli novu ogrlicu od bisera. (*princu*, indirect object of the verb) (They brought the prince a new pearl necklace.)
4. Bez obzira na sve, princ je odbio da odustane od svoje namere. (*princ*, subject of the sentence) (Regardless of everything, the prince refused to give up on his intention.)
5. Kada je princ stigao u grad, dočekali su ga velikim slavljem. (*princ*, subject of the sentence) (When the prince arrived in the city, he was greeted with a big celebration.)
6. Ovaj dvorac je nekada bio dom princa i princeze. (*princa*, genitive case) (This castle used to be the home of the prince and the princess.)
7. Kralj je princa proglasio za svog naslednika. (*princa*, direct object of the verb) (The king declared the prince his heir.)
8. Uprkos svojoj mladosti, princ je već bio veoma mudar. (*princ*, subject of the sentence) (Despite his youth, the prince was already very wise.)